# Styling Conventions

## Design Tokens

Always use CSS custom properties from the design system rather than hardcoded values.

```css
/* ❌ BAD - Hardcoded values */
button {
  padding: 10px 16px;
  border-radius: 4px;
  color: #374151;
}

/* ✅ GOOD - Use design tokens */
button {
  padding: var(--button-padding-y) var(--button-padding-x);
  border-radius: var(--radius-button);
  color: var(--color-text);
}
```

## Available Token Categories

- **Colors**: `--color-*` (bg, text, border variants)
- **Spacing**: `--spacing-*` (1-8 scale)
- **Typography**: `--body-font-*`, `--heading-font-*`
- **Sizing**: `--button-padding-*`, `--input-padding-*`
- **Borders**: `--radius-*`, `--border-width-*`

## Color Usage

```css
/* Background colors */
background-color: var(--color-bg);
background-color: var(--color-bg-elevated);
background-color: var(--color-bg-primary);

/* Text colors */
color: var(--color-text);
color: var(--color-text-secondary);
color: var(--color-text-on-primary);

/* Border colors */
border-color: var(--color-border);
```

## Responsive Design

- Use mobile-first approach
- Define breakpoints consistently
- Test on multiple screen sizes

```css
/* ✅ GOOD - Mobile first */
.cards-grid {
  grid-template-columns: 1fr;
  gap: var(--spacing-3);
}

@media (min-width: 768px) {
  .cards-grid {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: var(--spacing-element);
  }
}
```

## State Styles

Always style interactive states:

```css
/* ✅ GOOD - All states covered */
button {
  background-color: var(--color-bg-primary);
}

button:hover:not(:disabled) {
  background-color: var(--color-bg-primary-hovered);
}

button:focus-visible {
  outline: var(--focus-ring-width) solid var(--color-primary);
}

button:disabled {
  opacity: 0.6;
  cursor: not-allowed;
}
```

## Naming Conventions

- Use kebab-case for CSS class names
- Use descriptive names that indicate purpose
- Avoid overly specific selectors

```css
/* ✅ GOOD */
.book-list { }
.trending-covers { }
.password-input-wrapper { }

/* ❌ BAD */
.bl { }
.div1 { }
.container-wrapper-inner-box { }
```
